review 3: the place is comfortable and clean, very quiet and suitable for those who don't like noise, the cleanliness of the rooms is most satisfying, thank you to Bli Sony üëåüèª

review 5: This was a great stay. The rooms are well air conditioned and cleaned. The two ladies running the place were fabulous at their job and very friendly. The only complaint is that the road noise is a little loud.

They charged us inr 28000 for one night. They even asked us not to give negative reviews about the place. It's listed as villa. No basic amenities like water to drink also has to be paid for.. the other villas we stayed at Bali provided water cans. Don'topt for this place if going as a family. You'll regret
review 2: We booked and played mths ago . Only to be cancelled on the day before we arrive . This took 2 days to sort out . Asham as my holiday was ment to be stress free

name: Pondok Widji
address: C76F+9XC, Jl. Uma Aya, Batuan, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80582, Indonesia
review 1: This is perfect if you want a quiet place to relax and experiece the authentic Balinese culture. Set in the garden of an artist, it is close to many attractions (Bali Zoo, hidden canion, butterfly park, Bali bird park, temples and beaches) and Sukawati is a centre for painting, woodcarving and silver smiths, and has a huge art market. There are numerous restaurants within walking distance, The building is a delight, has a small kitchen and aircondition, is comfortable and is cleaned every day. The host Wayan and his wife Komang could not be more helpful, often presenting me with fruit from the garden and sharing a meal. I highly recommend this place as a base for exploring and immersing into the local culture
